 "components": {
  "instruction": "Given a piece of user text, your task is to classify it into exactly one of the following categories: alarm, apr, balance, book_flight, book_hotel, calculator, calories, car_rental, cook_time, credit_limit, credit_score, definition, direct_deposit, freeze_account, lost_luggage, meeting_schedule, pay_bill, payday, pto_request, recipe, report_fraud, report_lost_card, restaurant_reservation, restaurant_reviews, rewards_balance, taxes, timer, transfer, travel_suggestion, weather.\n\nKeep in mind the following important instructions:\n\n- Carefully analyze the input text and use context clues to determine the most appropriate category.\n- Pay special attention to legal and financial terms, especially for overlapping concepts. For example, if a user mentions their card was stolen or lost, classify as 'report_lost_card', not 'report_fraud'. Use 'report_fraud' when the text specifically concerns unauthorized transactions or suspicious activity, not just the loss/theft of a card.\n- If a text indicates making a reservation at a restaurant, choose 'restaurant_reservation'. If requesting or giving reviews/opinions about restaurants, select 'restaurant_reviews'.\n- For travel-related queries, choose the most specific intent: booking flights ('book_flight'), booking hotels ('book_hotel'), or renting cars ('car_rental'), and use 'travel_suggestion' only for open-ended travel recommendations or planning help.\n- When a text clearly requests information about a financial measure (e.g., 'What is my credit score?'), use the matching label (e.g., 'credit_score'). Use 'balance' for checking account or card balances, and 'rewards_balance' specifically for points or rewards programs.\n- If a user asks for help setting or managing a timer, select 'timer'; for setting an alarm, select 'alarm'.\n- For definitions or meanings of words, use 'definition'.\n- Use 'recipe' or 'cook_time' for food preparation queries as appropriate; 'recipe' for ingredients/instructions, 'cook_time' for time-only questions.\n- When a query could fit more than one category, prefer the most specific/targeted label.\n- Output only the category label from the provided list, and do not include any additional text in your response.\n\nCareful, precise, and context-sensitive label selection is required to avoid confusion between similar categories."
 },
